cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the need for modern data analytics to combine relational, procedural, and map-reduce-style functional processing, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also talks about optimizing query processing and code generation, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses machine learning kernels, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents a new back-end for Spark, which involves extending the scope of optimization and code generation to large classes of UDFs, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
